							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/marianaenriquez/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/mariana-enriquez-100x100.jpeg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/mariana-enriquez-300x300.jpeg 2x" alt="Mariana Enriquez" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/marianaenriquez/">Mariana Enriquez</a></h6>
										Mariana Enriquez is a writer based in Buenos Aires. She has published in English the novel <em>Our Share of Night</em> and three story collections, <em>A Sunny Place for Shady People</em>, <em>Things We Lost in the Fire</em>, and <em>The Dangers of Smoking in Bed</em>, which was a finalist for the International Booker Prize, the Kirkus Prize, the Ray Bradbury Prize for Science Fiction, Fantasy & Speculative Fiction, and the <em>Los Angeles Times</em> Book Prize in Fiction.																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
							</div>
